line_1: RIGHT wele of lerned clerkis is it sed,
line_2: That womenhud for mannis' use is made;

line_1: But naughty man liketh not one, or so,
line_2: He lusteth aye unthirftily for mo;

line_1: And whom he whilome cherished, when tied

line_1: Like unto dog which lighteth of a bone,
line_2: His tail he waggeth, glad therefore y-grown,

line_1: His tail he waggeth, glad therefore y-grown,
line_2: Like unto dog which lighteth of a bone,

line_1: But thilke same bone if to his tail thou tye,
line_2: Pardie, he fearing it away doth fly.
